node.text:
We place so much of our happiness into the hands of others.

So much of our worth, whether that’s feeling sexy or feeling adequate enough to be successful.

It’s not taught to us that we truly have the power to fulfill all our own needs. That statement itself gives me chills, because YOU can place that happiness within yourself.

You have the power to be your bestfriend, hype women, lover, and fufill the void that others aren’t filling.

So choose yourself, you fulfill your own needs.

node.title: One Affirmation That Can Change Your Life

node.text:
Want a healthy brownie that tastes EXACTLY like a real one?

I gotchu, stay hydrated b*tches. I make this every single night all cozy in my pjs-my favorite recipe I’ve posted yet!

Recipe:
1 tbsp dairy free butter
1/4 cup flour
1-1 1/2 tbsp coconut sugar
2 tbsp cocoa powder
1 scoop collagen protein
1 tsp vanilla
1 tbsp peanut butter
Splash of baking soda
1/4 cup water

Microwave for 1-2 minutes and enjoy an ooey gooey brownie!

#thedailysculpt #sculptyou

node.text:
Move over Mickey D’s we got some new nuggets in the house

I love making my own chicken nuggets at home (also can make in the air fryer) for a little snack with some ketchup, also helps beat fast food cravings!

All you need:
coconut or almond flour, egg whites, and panko. I seasoned mine with salt, paprika, and garlic!

Dip cut up chicken in the flour, egg whites, then panko. Put into the air fryer or oven at 400 for 10 minutes!

If you’re vegan you can use tofu and sub coconut oil for the egg whites!

Hope you all enjoy❤️🙏🏼

A mood after getting back to the gym after not lifting anything heavy for months or hearing loud sexual grunting 24/7

I am now ovulating and have pulled not just one but multiple of my hips

This is a complete comedic joke for anyone watching lmao, and please be careful getting back into the gym. Lose the ego and focus on form and not pushing extreme weight! Also take all the precautions necessary (without spraying someone entirely with Lysol) to protect yourself and others from the Coronavirus

Pls enjoy

node.text:
IT IS HERE

my favorite recipe of all time: healthy vegan donuts that you’ll want to have for dessert every night

Recipe:

INGREDIENTS
1 cup of flour (I used einkorn flour but you can also use whole wheat, pastry flour, or a gluten free 1–1 substitute)
1/2 teaspoon of baking soda
teaspoon of baking powder
pinch of salt
1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon
1/4 cup of maple syrup
1/2 cup of almond milk
3 tablespoons of nut butter
1 teaspoon of vanilla extract
1 medium banana, mashed

Mix all together and bake for 10 minutes at 350.

You can also put them into balls and make them in the air fryer or oven if you don’t have a donut pan!

#thedailysculpt #sculptyou

node.text:
Another Tuesday healthy recipe video coming @ you that is worth waiting until the end

Today we have grain free nachos with dairy free cheese!! When looking for potato chips or any plain chip, I like to go by the three or four ingredient rule. potato/grain, non inflammatory oil (avocado, coconut, etc), and sea salt

Will continue to bring you guys recipes every Tuesday, but will be bringing a twist to them!

My eyes have been more than opened to the racial injustices in our food and healthcare system, I plan on shining light on those and bringing to you all recipes that can be made with adorable ingredients you can find anywhere. Hope you all have a blessed day!! #thedailysculpt #sculptyou

node.text:
This is an absolute troll on my morning routine, please enjoy

But it rings true!! So important to have structure in the morning for myself. To set myself up with a focus for the day and come into the day with a clear mind/try to release any tension in my body

Every morning consists of my skincare routine, mediation (@thesculptyou or the calm app), and journaling.

Also I never chuck my journal off the balcony it was a one time stunt do not try that at home lmao

Figure out what works for you and start your day like a boss

#thedailysculpt #sculptyou

node.text:
One of my favorite recipes I’ve ever made, is finally here

High protein dairy free Mac and cheese coming at you

All you need is:
1/2 block or 1 small block of silken tofu
1/4 cup coconut milk
2 tsp (or more depending on your taste) of garlic salt
Dairy free cheese + butter I personally use @miyokoscreamery 
Elbow pasta

Blend tofu, milk, and garlic salt together to create a sauce. Mix with buttered elbow pasta, and top with cheese!

Hope you enjoy this recipe and let me know what you think if you try it out!

#thedailysculpt #sculptyou

node.text:
I absolutely love this question-and the answer is simple but very complex

Choose yourself.

I know what you’re thinking-wtf does that mean.

It means, look internally and see what you’re seeking from others.

It’s time to give that to yourself. When you are whole within yourself, you don’t need to seek outside validation because you provide it.

A partner adds to your life and elevates you-you don’t deserve to wait to be chosen. Step in and choose yourself.

#thedailysculpt #scultpyou

node.title: How To Get Over Someone Who Won’t Choose Me

node.text:
Tonight I’m bringing you 3 of my favorite super easy healthy desserts to curb that sweet tooth. All of these take less than 5 minutes!

Air fried dates: fill up a date with almond butter and place in air fryer for 3 minutes. Can also use a microwave! Top with chocolate and enjoy!

Fried Bananas: sauté bananas in a pan with coconut oil, cinnamon, honey, and Himalayan salt until crispy!

And the easiest one- put some chocolate into a raspberry and call it a night!

Hope you all enjoyed!

#thedailysculpt #sculptyou

node.text:
Bringing a new segment called chit chat with Kat!! I wanted to answer questions on all things lifestyle/love/relationships as mental and physical health doesn’t stop with the gym and nutrition, your mindset is everything

Trust me, I know the “mindset is everything” slogan can cause you to roll your eyes, because there’s so much pain/trauma behind every thought you may have.

But, these simple shifts build up. The simple realization to recognizing this life only has ONE of you can shift to then a daily dedication of you appreciating the deepest parts of your soul that nobody else has

Recognize your unique internal beauty, and know that reflects outwards. There are always going to be beautiful people on this earth, but that doesn’t take away anything from you-you are worthy

#thedailysculpt #sculptyou

node.title: “I don’t feel physically good enough for my man”

node.text:
Raw bathroom talk goin up on a Tuesday

Let’s talk self worth: how do you raise it?

Take a look at what you WANT to feel and WHO you want to be-you hold the power in who you want to create.

There’s been dark moments of my past, but I refuse to let it define my future as I live everyday creating someone I’m proud of. That’s where you build your self worth.

You are NOT worth feeling less than, take the reigns in your life. Don’t look back and settle for being treated less than you deserve, step into your power!

This is easier said than done, and a daily process. But I promise you, incredibly worth the work.

My May challenge closes tonight! So excited for this month with you all!

#thdailysculpt #sculptyou

node.text:
4 years ago I looked at myself in the mirror and said “please fight for me.”

I was barely eating, consuming alcohol or getting high whenever possible to distract my mind, I just took a medical leave from school unsure when I would be able to complete classes, and my boyfriend of 4 years recently broke up with me over text.

I just wanted to feel strong. I wanted to feel confident within who I was as a human being. I wanted to be able to experience life without constantly being worried about how I looked, what I was eating, and if I was “enough.”

I discovered the gym during this time, falling in love with how it made me feel. How my body was reflecting how strong I was feeling. Started to recognize the power of food and nutrition, how beautiful it was that we are able to experience food that nourishes us. That it wasn’t to be feared-but a form of self love.

Slowly-I started to be more present. Recognizing the earth doesn’t care what weight I am, it just wants me to experience it. Recognizing a number on the scale doesn’t mean shit-what matters is how I feel within myself. I kept showing up to find a way of training/eating that allowed me to experience life in a way that makes me happy.

I kept showing up to look back into the mirror and feel acceptance for who I’m becoming. Not a person whose worth was defined by how many workouts they hit that week/a number.

(& we are proud of the booty and strength gains that have come from it‼️)

node.text:
Doing this for the girl who never believed she could get out of her toxic relationship, the girl who never believed she would be able to eat food without thinking she had to “burn it off” right away, the girl who just wanted to feel enough. The girl who just wanted to be chosen.

I chose myself. And I wish I could hug my past self and tell her it’s going to be alright, I know she would’ve done anything to hear those words. But every single thing I did during those dark times-every breathless painful cry into my pillow, every therapy session, every second spent alone, every second terrified, every time I asked why I wasn’t enough.. lead me to wanting to finally choose myself. To discover my worth isn’t dictated by someone else, or their inability to see mine, but by me.

So if you feel stuck right now, I hope I can be the voice that tells you you’re worth fighting for. No matter how long it takes, baby steps every day backward or forward is bringing you to the version of yourself you are fighting to create.

Also reminder everyone starts in the gym not knowing wtf to do, and it took me some damn time to figure it out-RIP to that hip thrust form☠️

Sending the most love possible❤️

node.text:
No need to go to Arby’s: we have the MEATS‼️ here’s a 🔥 quad focused leg day for you

For front squats: the bar should rest on the “shelf” that you have created by lifting your delts up and forward. Aka it should not be resting on bone! It’s definitely an uncomfortable movement and takes some getting used to, so focus on form/control/comfortability over everything. I personally rest the bar on my “delt shelf”, and cross my hands over it for more stability due to my lack of wrist mobility.

If you are struggling with picking the weight off the ground for a set, highly recommend utilizing the bench! Set your weight there, and preform your squat from the bench height with the dumbbell in hand. I utilize this technique for split squats as well so I’m not straining my lower back picking both off the floor.

Hope you enjoy this 🔥 quad & booty workout, first workout to kick off my September challenge!

node.text:
REMINDER: rest days and recovery are necessary for muscle growth + repair, AND YOU WONT LOSE ALL YOUR MUSCLE WITH TIME OFF THE GYM! Your mind is lying to you!

Building muscle is a slow timely process…and once you’ve built a solid foundation your body doesn’t let it disappear so easily. So we can let go of the thoughts that if we are out of the gym for a couple days, a week, two weeks +, that all our progress will be lost.  Let’s also let go of the thought that we have to be in the gym every single day to see results-you are creating microscopic tears in your muscle every time you train muscle groups, they need time and fuel to rebuild & recover!

What you can do if you will be out of the gym for some time and want to maintain muscle:
1) EAT‼️ consume your maintenance or slightly above
2) eat an adequate amount of protein
3) if you’re able to get in movement, any movement is great! Walking, dancing, yoga etc

Another reminder that your worth isn’t dictated by muscle mass. I’ve been out of the gym for months due to my mental health, surgeries, traveling etc during my fitness journey-it was necessary for my own healing, and created an internal strength I didn’t know I had. And I didn’t lose muscle during this time period-so focus on how your body feels and needs over everything!🤍

node.text:
Are you ready to discover the secret formula to the Krabby Phatty? My @thesculptyou September challenge is now LIVE! Link in bio, sign ups close midnight on September 4th.

All of us have felt like plankton-searching for the secret formula that will lead us to our happiest and healthiest life. We try to copy and put together ingredients from others who seem to have it all figured out-just to feel like the damn chumbucket. Because the truth is-even if we all use the EXACT SAME ingredients, each of us will end up looking and feeling different.

That’s why at @thesculptyou, my goal is to provide you the tools to discover your own secret formula for what works for you. For $9 a month we provide daily home AND gym workouts (that follow a full body monthly split), 4 weekly meal plans written by our RD (lifestyle, hormone health, vegan, gluten/soy/dairy free) with a macro tracking section OR intuitive eating section, a mental health section with yoga/breathwork/meditation, and an educational period tracker to help you during each phase of your cycle, daily journal prompts and more.

Like spongebob says IM MFING READY‼️ so excited for this month and can’t even tell you how appreciate I am of the energy you all bring to this program each and every day.

node.text:
You know the vibe‼️‼️ s/o to my IBS for always workin hard, but the dairy free section stays workin harder

Like many others, my wellness journey has been pretty lonely. Have y’all felt that way? Finding your own inner strength to put yourself and your health first, fighting your own negative self talk, aligning more with things that elevate you…it can become a path where you lose people who don’t support or align with the person you’re growing into. It can take a lot of energy focusing on yourself, where it becomes too much to extend to others. This includes trying to meet others who align with your passions, which is difficult in itself. And not only does it create a deep feeling of loneliness, but shame for not being able to have many genuine and amazing connections

This feeling intensified as my mental health declined and as I was diagnosed with IC, IBS, and post concussion syndrome. Alcohol intensified my symptoms so I cut back on drinking, my anxiety kept me to my room, and my IBS/IC caused fear of food which I then struggled eating outside the house.

Writing this for others who may also feel a deep sense of loneliness or lack of support/understanding for their wellness journeys. Writing this so these words hopefully feel like a hug, so that you know there’s NO shame. This is a powerful part of your journey, to discover the strength of becoming YOUR friend first and foremost. When you align with this, amazing things happen.

& this is always why I am so proud of The Sculpt Squad community @thesculptyou, seeing real genuine support & friendships develop is all I could ever ask for. So excited for another month of challenges with y’all tomorrow❤️

node.text:
Do you deadlift with small plates or no plates? Or don’t use a standard 45 pound plate? This is for you⬇️

Not deadlifting at the correct height for your body can put a lot of stress on your lower back/hips, and leads to unsafe form preformed. Plus you aren’t getting the true benefits of the deadlift without proper form!

Solution: put some plates under the barbell to raise the barbell up about 9 inches, slightly below the middle of your shin on majority of people. This also may work if you use a 45 pound plate and your form is at risk due to your height/hip mobility.

Deadlifts are my absolute favorite full body movement, so try this out to reap all the benefits & protect your body from injury!

node.text:
Do you only feel your quads during hip thrusts? Struggle with really feeling those GLUTES without hurting your lower back?

One of my favorite variations of the hip thrust: the glute scoop (majority of people feel this variation in their glutes more! And helps prevent overextending of lower back, which is what we are talking about when we say anterior pelvic tilt!)

Keep your chin tucked to your chest, mostly moving from the ribs down, and focus on “scooping” your hips under at the top. I also have my feet slightly pointed outwards as this helps me engage my glutes more.

As always let me know if you have any questions! Also y’all are welcome for this BOP, the part where Bryson tiller comes in 🥵 oh lawd

node.text:
They say one of the only times you should look back is to see how far you’ve come…but what if you keep looking back wishing you could still be that version of yourself?

Do you find yourself saying “I looked better then” and immediately shame your body how it is now?

Maybe it’s “I was more disciplined then” or “I used to be more motivated.”

Maybe it’s.. I miss the version of myself that I was before I experienced this heart break.

We tend to immediately shame our present selves, not seeing how much our body & mind have been through. Not seeing that as humans we will never stay the same-we go through different experiences everyday that alter us. That past version of yourself doesn’t exist anymore, as all those shitty moments & beautiful moments created an even greater version of you.

You may sit there and wonder how I can say “greater.” Greater because without you even recognizing it, you’ve proven to yourself everyday that you can survive your thoughts. Even when it feels impossible to.

So while you may miss that older version, take a moment and really think about what your body has experienced. This version of you NOW is more capable than you can even imagine.

I hope that instills a fire in you to remember fondly some aspects of the chapters of your story, but to keep writing. Every good book keeps you so excited to keep turning the page and not flip backwards.

If I choose to put myself in my personal hell and get bitch slapped by these weights…these cheeks better wake tf up‼️‼️ it ain’t sleepy time

So what if you’ve been doing your basic compound movements (squats, deadlifts, lunges) + hip thrusts and haven’t seen any change?

A couple things to look at:
🤍INTENTION. Are you performing the movement to almost failure? Utilizing the heaviest weight you can with proper form? Maximizing tension/mind muscle connection during each rep? Slowing your movements down?
🤍FORM. Are you prioritizing form over weights? Prioritizing core strength/hip mobility/ankle mobility?
🤍STRUCTURED PROGRAM. Are you following a structured program and doing these movements here and there with various rep ranges? Focusing on progressive overload?
🤍CALORIC INTAKE. Are you eating enough to fuel muscle growth? Is your protein/carb intake consistent?
🤍MENTAL HEALTH. Are you taking care of you? Sleep/stress? As these factors all contribute to muscle growth! Prioritizing your mental>than hitting the gym. A healthy body IS a healthy mind.

Lastly remember bioindividuality doesn’t just play a role in nutrition, but also training. Play around with where you feel the most optimal contraction/tension. Find what movements feel best for you, or variants of them.

Let me know if you have any questions below!❤️
